Expectant mothers attending antenatal at the Soba Comprehensive Health Centre in Soba Local Government Area of Kaduna State have received maternity packs from the Sani Dauda Foundation. Arewa Trust Weekly reports that a total of 20 expectant mothers got a pack each of maternity items, consisting of a wrapper, delivery kits, delivery kits, sanitary packs, post-delivery childcare products and baby clothing worth N30,000. In her speech at the occasion, the wife of the proprietor of Sani Dauda Foundation, Hajiya Maryam Sani Dauda, said the donation is in continuation of the foundationâ€™s assistance to the needy in the society. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE She prayed to Almighty Allah to grant the expectant mothers safe delivery and urged them to always attend antenatal clinics during pregnancy and ensure that their kids receive vaccinations after birth. The beneficiaries thanked the foundation for the gesture. Asokoro Rotary Club begins maternal/child mortality prevention campaign Foundation donates birth kits to IDPs Foundation donates maternity packs to women Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin